Determining Color¶

In [0]:
def getColorName(data, bgr):
    '''
    Input:
        data => DataFrame having column-data in the format - (r, g, b, color_name)
        rgb => Array/List of rgb values
    Output:
        Returns color_name that matches the most rgb values on the basis of distance
    '''
    
    tmp = float('inf')
    for i in range(data.shape[0]):
        d = abs(bgr[2] - int(data.iloc[i, 0])) + abs(bgr[1] - int(data.iloc[i, 1])) + abs(bgr[0] - int(data.iloc[i, 2]))
        if(d<tmp):
            tmp = d
            cname = data.iloc[i, 3]
    return cname

Retrieve Image-Data¶

In [0]:
def retriev_data(event, x, y, flags, params):
    '''
    A callback function for mouse-click.
    
    Checks for 'Mouse Left button double click' & returns back it's corresponding rgb values
    '''
    
    if(event==cv2.EVENT_LBUTTONDBLCLK):
        params['clicked'] = True
        params['bgr'] = params['image'][y, x]
In [0]:
def img_data(data, image, clickable=False):
    '''
    Input:
        image => Image as numpy array
        clickable => if True, user will get to select the pixel point by mouse double-click
                     if False, center pixel point of image will be taken into consideration
    Output:
        Returns rgb values of the pixel point
    '''

    if(clickable):
        global params
        params = {
            'clicked': False,
            'image': image,
            'bgr': None
        }
        cv2.namedWindow('Image')
        cv2.setMouseCallback('Image', retriev_data, params)
    
        while(True):
            cv2.imshow('Image', image)

            if(params['clicked']):
                params['clicked'] = False
                print(getColorName(data=data, bgr=params['bgr']))
                break

            if(cv2.waitKey(20) & 0xFF==27):  # escape key
                print('Error')
                break
        cv2.destroyAllWindows()
    
    else:
        return print(getColorName(data=data, bgr=image[image.shape[0]//2, image.shape[1]//2]))

Creating Model¶

In [19]:
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(width, height, channels)),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),
    tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=128, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=3, activation='softmax')
])

model.summary()

# Training data
train_datagen = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1/255,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest'
)

train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    '/tmp/Data/train/',
    target_size=(width, height),
    batch_size=25,
    class_mode='categorical'
)

# Validation data
validate_datagen = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1/255
)

validate_generator = validate_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    '/tmp/Data/validation/',
    target_size=(width, height),
    batch_size=25,
    class_mode='categorical'
)
